body:
The CI build was failing when the smoke test `ensureStableCode()` function encountered errors during stable VS Code download. This function can fail due to:

- Network timeouts when fetching release data from the VS Code update server
- Download failures of the stable VS Code binary 
- File system issues during extraction
- Missing suitable stable version for the current build

When these errors occurred during the global `before()` hook setup, they would crash the entire test suite, even though individual data-loss tests are designed to gracefully skip when stable code is unavailable.

**Before this fix:**
```typescript
// Any error here crashes the entire test suite
await measureAndLog(() => ensureStableCode(), 'ensureStableCode', logger);
```

**After this fix:**
```typescript
try {
    await measureAndLog(() => ensureStableCode(), 'ensureStableCode', logger);
} catch (error) {
    logger.log(`Failed to ensure stable code: ${error}. Data loss tests will be skipped.`);
    // Don't throw - let individual tests handle missing stable code gracefully
}
```

This change makes the test infrastructure more resilient to transient CI environment issues while preserving existing functionality. Data-loss tests continue to skip themselves when stable code is unavailable, but setup failures no longer crash the entire suite.

Applied the same fix to both smoke test (`test/smoke/src/main.ts`) and MCP test (`test/mcp/src/application.ts`) infrastructures for consistency.

Fixes #267275.

